In every other game this world was playable, all you did was walk up the steps to see a cutscene and then leave immediately after. We've lost nothing with this change

(yes a mushroom 13 member appeared there in 2 but we don't talk about them)

Jungle Book (Birth By Sleep):
This one is my least favorite call in this whole thread. They cut this world because the Peter Pan world was already Jungly enough. Why not cut the world we've been to already instead?! Also this would've been a great replacement for Tarzan.

Pinocchio's World (358/2 Days):
I would've liked the change of scenery, but I think they made the right call in waiting until 3D to have us visit there. There, it worked great with Sora learning his friend's past and Riku fighting his past.

Deep Jungle (Chain of Memories):
Okay, I will defend Deep Jungle to the ends of the earth... BUT, if they somehow mashed that world into a GBA game, I feel like it would've been a disaster.

Overall, I'm sad about the Tarzan rights situation, but I guess it is what it is...

Toy Story (Kingdom Hearts 1 and 2):
In both KH1 (allegedly) and KH2 (in the game's coding) there are scraps from Toy Story that implies that they could've gotten a world.

Either way, we ended up getting it in KH3 and I think the wait made it even more worthwhile.

Disney Castle (Kingdom Hearts 1):
You were meant to be able to visit the place and do something there.

If it's anything like KH2's Disney Castle, then I'd say we've dodged a bullet.

Actually, what if KH2s plot point there was meant for KH1. Guess we'll never know.

THREAD:
This is a thread of my game lists throughout the years.

From now on, I'm gonna be rating all the games I played through throughout each year in each December.

And in last place, here's Doctor Mario World.

Just like Paper Jam, this game fucked up a great idea, but Paper Jam goes miles above this one because at least it was fun throughout the experience

This game was only enjoyable in it's dying breath when they turned off the P2W shit https://t.co/dbQFY1oFlr

Nearing the bottom, we've got Mario and Luigi Paper Jam.

The game is FINE, but for a crossover between my two favorite Mario spinoffs, this game was a HUGE letdown.

Bowser's Inside Story remake can share a spot with Paper Jam since it was the final nail in AlphaDream's coffin. https://t.co/Cds1tQOzqP

Next is Pokémon Ranger 1.

If you played Pokémon Ranger 2 or Pokémon Ranger 3, DO NOT PLAY THIS GAME. It aged like microwaved yogurt.

The only thing this game has going for it is that it kicked off the Pokémon Ranger series. Otherwise this game is absolutely outdated. https://t.co/UprOIB3iGj

Next is Mario 35

This game rivaled Puyo Puyo Tetris and Ranger 2. This game would've been at the top if not for ONE thing…

The reason this game is on the bottom half of this list is because it was released with an expiration date. They flushed this amazing idea down the toilet https://t.co/34K1JSEVVZ

Next is Pokémon Ranger 3.

This game is a downgrade from Pokémon Ranger 2 in most aspects and that disappoints me.

My main issues are:
1. Half of the QoLs from 2 were removed
2. 100%ing the past

I should mention that it's still a great game, but it's severely held back... https://t.co/73LIxe6oG9

Another very close runner up and my biggest surprise this year goes to Dream Team

After Sticker Star, I lost hope in Mario RPGs overall. Coming back to this was my best choice ever. It's now my second favorite M&L game

I'm also gonna give this spot to the Superstar Saga remake https://t.co/nkXI8JM66d

A very close second place goes to Pokémon Ranger 2. This game takes this spinoff series' gimmick to the absolute best. I put 100 hours into 100%ing it and not a single hour was spent doing the same thing. The story is great and the side quests are fun and rewarding. https://t.co/fi83AQbuO1

My personal Game of the Year is Puyo Puyo Tetris and Puyo Puyo Tetris 2

This was the most enjoyable duo of games to 100% throughout the entire year and I totally see myself playing them even more given the chance

They also have amazing multiplayer and great overall presentation https://t.co/QNc7ZJFhu1
